#: ../../../release_details/9.4/macro-semi-colons.md:1
msgid "Some function-like macros now require trailing semi-colons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/macro-semi-colons.md:3
msgid ""
"Function-like macros such as vtkVLog, vtkLog, vtkVLogIf, vtkLogIf, "
"vtkOpenGLCheckErrorMacro, vtkOpenGLStaticCheckErrorMacro, and "
"vtkOpenGLDebugCheckErrorMacro (and perhaps more, that are implemented using "
"them), now require a trailing semi-colon where invoked.  For example, this "
"would have previously compiled:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/macro-semi-colons.md:5
msgid "vtkLog(ERROR, \"No output data.\")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/macro-semi-colons.md:9
msgid "but now *must* be written as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/macro-semi-colons.md:11
msgid "vtkLog(ERROR, \"No output data.\");\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/macro-semi-colons.md:15
msgid ""
"Adding the semi-colon will result in code that compiles both before and "
"after this change, and so your code can still be compatible with old and new "
"VTK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/macro-semi-colons.md:17
msgid ""
"This change was motivated by making the VTK codebase compile cleanly with "
"the clang `-Wextra-semi-stmt` warning."
msgstr ""
